## Why This Is Asked

Tests practical streaming patterns under privacy, schema evolution, and data-contract constraints, plus real-world trade-offs between Spark and Flink.

## Key Concepts

- Contract-first schemas (Avro/Protobuf) for events
- Per-record privacy masking at ingest
- Iceberg MERGE-based upserts with transactional writes
- Bounded late data window (15 minutes) for backfill
- Per-record lineage and observability

